## Findings
- Video title: AI뉴스 - Google 신모델, COSMO, Claude 요금 논란, Codex goal, Grok 4.3 API, Stripe AI Agent 지갑, HappyHorse 등
- Video key points:
    - Google Gemini Flash new model released.
    - Google Omni video model testing.
    - Cosmo App leak (Google).
    - Gemini File creation feature.
    - Mention of GPT-5.5 release in suggested videos.
- Model comparison (Detailed):
    - **GPT-5 / 5.5 (OpenAI)**: The "Agentic" flagship. Specialized in autonomous tasks and general reasoning. $10/M tokens (In), $30/M tokens (Out).
    - **Claude Opus 4.5 / 4.8 (Anthropic)**: The "Technical" leader. Best for Software Development, vision, and high accuracy. $15/M (In), $75/M (Out). 200K context.
    - **Gemini 2.0 Ultra (Google)**: The "Scientific" powerhouse. Best for multi-modal reasoning and Google ecosystem integration.
    - **DeepSeek V4**: High-performance, low-cost coding alternative.
- Free vs Paid:
    - **Free**: Local Gemma (0 cost), Claude/ChatGPT/Gemini limited free tiers (Haiku/Flash models).
    - **Paid**: API-based token pricing (shown above) or $20-30/month Pro subscriptions for unlimited web access.
- Hybrid strategies:
    - **Local Gemma**: Use for privacy, formatting, simple classification, and pre-processing.
    - **Cloud Models**: Use for high-stakes reasoning, complex coding, and final "Quality Gates".
    - **Flow**: Local Gemma (Pre-process/Filter) -> Cloud (Complex Reasoning) -> Local Gemma (Post-process/Format).
